cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of diagnostic classification of lung nodules in CT images using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks for classification also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being a relevant sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of transfer learning, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of CT images suggests that medical imaging (cs.MM) could also be a relevant sub-category.
